The paper deals with dynamic subgraph connectivity problems for planar graphs, which is a topic in graph algorithms and data structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves some combinatorial aspects, such as the use of Barnette's theorem, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as another possible sub-category. The paper also presents optimal algorithms, which may fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
